# Auto-push to GitHub

After making any substantive edits to the project (HTML, CSS, JS, content, or config):

1. Run in project root (`ии`):  
   `git add -A`  
   `git status` (to confirm what will be committed)
2. Commit with a short message describing the change, e.g.:  
   `git commit -m "Add FAQ section"` or `git commit -m "Fix hero layout"`
3. Push to origin:  
   `git push origin main`

Use a single commit per logical change; avoid committing unrelated edits in one message. If the user only asked for analysis or no files were changed, skip git steps.
